1
00:00:41,959 --> 00:00:46,588
November 1958,
my senior year of high school.

2
00:00:46,630 --> 00:00:48,715
While other girls
were dancing to Elvis...

3
00:00:48,757 --> 00:00:50,300
and dreaming about prom dates...

4
00:00:50,342 --> 00:00:53,595
I was reading Jane Austen
and dreaming about college.

5
00:00:53,637 --> 00:00:55,305
And then my parents announced...

6
00:00:55,347 --> 00:00:57,683
we were moving to Cuba--
in a week.

7
00:01:09,027 --> 00:01:11,154
Slamming doors and
giving the silent treatment...

8
00:01:11,196 --> 00:01:12,614
couldn't change that...

9
00:01:12,656 --> 00:01:15,242
but it was easier than admitting
I was really scared.

10
00:01:15,284 --> 00:01:17,077
At least everyone else
was happy.

11
00:01:17,119 --> 00:01:19,246
Dad got his big promotion
from Ford.

12
00:01:19,288 --> 00:01:21,748
Mom got to travel in style,
and Susie...

13
00:01:21,790 --> 00:01:25,544
I swear that girl
could adjust in a hurricane.

14
00:02:29,107 --> 00:02:31,109
Welcome to the Hotel Oceana.

15
00:02:54,383 --> 00:02:56,593
Not too shabby, huh?

16
00:02:58,303 --> 00:02:59,888
Here's what I know about Cuba--

17
00:02:59,930 --> 00:03:02,474
my high-school French
wasn't going to help me.

18
00:03:02,516 --> 00:03:04,309
I didn't know a single person...

19
00:03:04,351 --> 00:03:06,019
and though no one
would talk about it...

20
00:03:06,061 --> 00:03:08,564
Fidel Castro was leading
a people in a revolution...

21
00:03:08,605 --> 00:03:10,732
against President Batista...

22
00:03:10,774 --> 00:03:13,986
not that you would know it
from this place.

23
00:03:16,989 --> 00:03:19,950
This is Cuba.
Nobody cares what you do here.

24
00:03:19,992 --> 00:03:21,493
Susie, you want a smoke?

25
00:03:21,535 --> 00:03:24,079
Watch out for this one.
She's a bad influence.

26
00:03:24,121 --> 00:03:25,831
I'll take that as a compliment.

27
00:03:25,873 --> 00:03:28,584
She'll have you
ditching classes in no time.

28
00:03:28,625 --> 00:03:30,377
As I recall,
there's a certain someone...

29
00:03:30,419 --> 00:03:31,962
that likes to ditch them
with me.

30
00:03:33,422 --> 00:03:36,175
Don't forget to sign up
for mambo lessons.

31
00:03:36,216 --> 00:03:38,385
Mambo classes
are held every day...

32
00:03:38,427 --> 00:03:41,305
My God.
June Cleaver is in Havana.

33
00:03:42,723 --> 00:03:46,435
Actually, that's my sister
Katey. She's a real brain.

34
00:03:46,476 --> 00:03:48,187
Oh, really?

35
00:03:48,228 --> 00:03:50,397
Yeah. She's probably going
to Radcliffe.

36
00:03:50,439 --> 00:03:52,191
What, majoring in fashion?

37
00:03:55,027 --> 00:03:58,906
Why don't you join us?
There's room here.

38
00:04:05,287 --> 00:04:06,830
I'm James Phelps.

39
00:04:06,872 --> 00:04:08,207
Hi. Katey Miller.

40
00:04:08,248 --> 00:04:09,541
Pleasure to meet you.

41
00:04:10,792 --> 00:04:12,085
- Are you the--
- Yeah.

42
00:04:12,127 --> 00:04:15,297
- Your dad works for my dad.
- Yeah.

43
00:04:15,339 --> 00:04:19,176
This is Sheila, Eve,
Polly, and Steph...

44
00:04:19,218 --> 00:04:21,094
and I guess you know Susie,
right?

45
00:04:22,763 --> 00:04:24,097
So, are you really going
to Radcliffe?

46
00:04:24,139 --> 00:04:25,557
I won't know till spring.

47
00:04:25,599 --> 00:04:28,101
Whoa. Watch out, girls.

48
00:04:28,143 --> 00:04:29,811
I guess if your head's
in your books...

49
00:04:29,853 --> 00:04:30,979
you really don't have time...

50
00:04:31,021 --> 00:04:34,900
to think about
silly things like the weather.

51
00:04:34,942 --> 00:04:36,193
Chilly?

52
00:04:37,319 --> 00:04:38,946
Oh.

53
00:04:40,322 --> 00:04:43,200
I'm so sorry. It's my fault.

54
00:04:43,242 --> 00:04:45,994
No, just go get new drinks.

55
00:04:51,458 --> 00:04:52,960
Stupid spic.

56
00:04:56,797 --> 00:04:58,465
Excuse me.

57
00:05:08,308 --> 00:05:10,769
- Excuse me. Señor?
- How may I help you, señorita?

58
00:05:10,811 --> 00:05:13,146
I knocked into those drinks.
I'd like to pay for them.

59
00:05:13,188 --> 00:05:16,775
That will not be necessary.
Accidents happen. Excuse me.

60
00:05:21,697 --> 00:05:24,658
I speak English...

61
00:05:24,700 --> 00:05:26,994
and I don't need your charity.

62
00:05:27,035 --> 00:05:29,454
It's not.

63
00:05:29,496 --> 00:05:31,456
Don't worry about it. It's OK.

64
00:05:33,709 --> 00:05:35,502
I'm sorry
for what she called you.

65
00:05:35,544 --> 00:05:37,379
- That was nothing.
- Not to me.

66
00:05:37,421 --> 00:05:39,548
Then why are you apologizing?

67
00:05:47,931 --> 00:05:49,683
You guys were so good.

68
00:05:49,725 --> 00:05:54,771
Your mother was good. I was OK.

69
00:05:54,813 --> 00:05:56,732
- Dad?
- Hmm.

70
00:05:56,773 --> 00:06:02,196
I'm sorry I haven't been
excited about all of this.

71
00:06:04,948 --> 00:06:06,283
Sweetheart, it's OK.

72
00:06:06,325 --> 00:06:10,537
Senior year is a terrible time
to drag you out of school...

73
00:06:10,579 --> 00:06:12,331
especially when
you're the star of the class.

74
00:06:12,372 --> 00:06:14,583
- Dad.
- Come on. Don't deny it.

75
00:06:14,625 --> 00:06:16,460
Be proud of it.

76
00:06:16,502 --> 00:06:19,922
You'll do great here, too.

77
00:06:33,769 --> 00:06:36,647
I can't stand on your feet
anymore.

78
00:06:42,611 --> 00:06:44,947
- Hey, you remembered that.
- Yeah.

79
00:06:46,323 --> 00:06:48,325
Very good.

80
00:06:51,203 --> 00:06:53,121
Let's continue
where we left off.

81
00:06:53,163 --> 00:06:56,250
Book 18, page 25.

82
00:06:56,291 --> 00:06:58,669
Katey, just do your best
to follow, all right?

83
00:06:58,710 --> 00:07:00,712
It's OK. I read it last year.

84
00:07:01,839 --> 00:07:03,841
Knock it off.

85
00:07:03,882 --> 00:07:07,010
Well, then perhaps you'd like
to begin reading at line 342.

86
00:07:08,846 --> 00:07:12,099
"Now the suitors
turned to dance and song...

87
00:07:12,140 --> 00:07:14,268
"to the lovely beaten sway...

88
00:07:14,309 --> 00:07:17,813
"waiting for dusk
to come upon them there...

89
00:07:17,855 --> 00:07:22,317
and the dark night came
upon them, lost in pleasure."

90
00:07:25,445 --> 00:07:27,489
Can anyone tell us...

91
00:07:27,531 --> 00:07:30,701
the significance
of this passage?

92
00:07:30,742 --> 00:07:33,245
It's a bunch of drunk guys
doing it.

93
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:43,172
Athena wants the suitors to
keep invading Odysseus' house...

94
00:07:43,213 --> 00:07:45,632
so that he'll get angry enough
to kill them.

95
00:07:45,674 --> 00:07:47,634
And why does the goddess
want that?

96
00:07:50,220 --> 00:07:54,183
She wants Odysseus
to find his strength...

97
00:07:54,224 --> 00:07:55,893
and courage?

98
00:07:55,934 --> 00:07:57,269
Very good.

99
00:08:13,577 --> 00:08:14,828
Need a ride home?

100
00:08:18,040 --> 00:08:22,294
No. I'm OK. I got
a lot of catching up to do.

101
00:08:22,336 --> 00:08:23,462
You know, a lot of girls...

102
00:08:23,504 --> 00:08:24,880
don't like to let on
when they're smart.

103
00:08:24,922 --> 00:08:26,465
I know.
I shouldn't have said--

104
00:08:26,507 --> 00:08:28,842
No. No, I like that.

105
00:08:28,884 --> 00:08:31,094
I like that about you.

106
00:08:34,973 --> 00:08:38,894
A bunch of us are going to our
country club on Saturday night.

107
00:08:38,894 --> 00:08:42,648
There'll be a band.
The music's pretty cool.

108
00:08:44,358 --> 00:08:46,109
Would you like to go with me?

109
00:08:46,151 --> 00:08:49,571
I really do have
a lot of work to do.

110
00:08:49,613 --> 00:08:50,864
On a Saturday night?

111
00:08:52,032 --> 00:08:53,659
Wow.

112
00:08:53,700 --> 00:08:57,746
Come on. I'm sure even Homer
took some time off...

113
00:08:57,788 --> 00:08:59,873
between The Iliad
and The Odyssey.

114
00:09:01,458 --> 00:09:03,877
Well, sure. OK.

115
00:09:03,919 --> 00:09:06,171
OK.

116
00:09:12,845 --> 00:09:14,888
We're all here now. You can go.

117
00:09:40,539 --> 00:09:41,748
Bonita.

118
00:10:52,778 --> 00:10:53,779
Eso.

119
00:11:06,583 --> 00:11:08,961
You felt the sudden urge
for Cuban music?

120
00:11:09,002 --> 00:11:11,380
The van left without me.

121
00:11:11,421 --> 00:11:12,756
I've been walking
for an hour.

122
00:11:12,798 --> 00:11:14,091
I can walk you back.

123
00:11:14,132 --> 00:11:15,717
Oh, no. You don't
have to do that.

124
00:11:15,759 --> 00:11:17,594
Oh, yeah, you're right.

125
00:11:17,636 --> 00:11:19,471
You'll find your way
sooner or later.

126
00:11:19,513 --> 00:11:22,224
Maybe in a week or a month.

127
00:11:22,266 --> 00:11:24,309
Let me just say good-bye.

128
00:11:24,351 --> 00:11:26,520
¡Abuelito!

129
00:11:32,943 --> 00:11:34,528
Bueno.

130
00:11:37,406 --> 00:11:38,365
What was it you called him?

131
00:11:38,407 --> 00:11:41,869
Abuelito. It's my grandpa.

132
00:11:43,328 --> 00:11:45,330
I'm Katey.
What's your name?

133
00:11:45,372 --> 00:11:47,249
Javier.

134
00:11:47,291 --> 00:11:51,378
So what, you know like
five words in Spanish?

135
00:11:51,420 --> 00:11:53,589
Maybe ten.

136
00:11:53,630 --> 00:11:55,841
And what are you
studying so hard to do?

137
00:11:55,883 --> 00:11:57,885
I haven't figured it out yet.

138
00:11:57,926 --> 00:12:00,470
Here. Let me take that.

139
00:12:05,184 --> 00:12:08,187
I've never seen
dancing like that.

140
00:12:08,228 --> 00:12:09,646
Like what?

141
00:12:09,688 --> 00:12:12,608
I don't know.

142
00:12:12,608 --> 00:12:15,319
I like it. It's very...

143
00:12:19,740 --> 00:12:21,950
- Very Cuban?
- Yeah.

144
00:12:50,312 --> 00:12:52,481
- We should get off the street.
- Why?

145
00:12:52,523 --> 00:12:54,608
You don't understand
what they're singing.

146
00:13:00,614 --> 00:13:02,783
No!

147
00:13:02,824 --> 00:13:03,992
No!

148
00:13:04,034 --> 00:13:06,286
That way!

149
00:13:08,080 --> 00:13:10,624
So you've got--
OK. Here she comes.

150
00:13:10,666 --> 00:13:12,543
Thank you so much.

151
00:13:12,584 --> 00:13:16,672
Thank God.
Katey, where have you been?

152
00:13:16,713 --> 00:13:18,841
I missed the bus.

153
00:13:18,882 --> 00:13:20,342
I'm fine. I walked.

154
00:13:20,384 --> 00:13:23,220
For heaven's sakes.
Katey, why didn't you call me?

155
00:13:23,262 --> 00:13:26,265
For all I knew, you could have
been kidnapped by rebels.

156
00:13:26,306 --> 00:13:29,184
It's not the rebels
you should be worried about.

157
00:13:29,226 --> 00:13:30,477
What did you say?

158
00:13:34,690 --> 00:13:38,402
You're right. I'm sorry.
I should have called.

159
00:13:38,443 --> 00:13:39,736
Honey, where's your book bag?

160
00:13:43,365 --> 00:13:45,576
I left it at school.

161
00:13:45,617 --> 00:13:46,743
It was heavy.

162
00:14:37,419 --> 00:14:39,087
Oh, God.

163
00:14:39,129 --> 00:14:42,382
It was good I had all these
boring American books with me.

164
00:14:42,424 --> 00:14:45,093
They realized I couldn't
be a revolutionary.

165
00:14:45,135 --> 00:14:47,513
I don't understand.

166
00:14:47,554 --> 00:14:48,847
They were just singing.

167
00:14:48,889 --> 00:14:51,808
There is not such a thing
as "just singing" here anymore.

168
00:14:55,062 --> 00:14:57,689
You know,
you're a pretty good dancer.

169
00:14:57,731 --> 00:15:00,776
I was terrible.

170
00:15:00,817 --> 00:15:04,613
Oh, yeah.
Yeah, you were terrible...

171
00:15:04,655 --> 00:15:07,115
but for an American,
you move well.

172
00:15:07,157 --> 00:15:08,784
Oh, thanks.

173
00:15:13,705 --> 00:15:15,916
Why do you look
in the mirror?

174
00:15:15,958 --> 00:15:18,585
I was trying to remember
the steps I saw.

175
00:15:18,627 --> 00:15:21,755
But what does looking
have to do with it?

176
00:15:21,797 --> 00:15:24,216
Just feel the music.

177
00:15:24,258 --> 00:15:26,176
You should see for yourself.

178
00:15:26,218 --> 00:15:30,639
The real dancers are at
La Rosa Negra on Saturday night.

179
00:15:33,308 --> 00:15:34,977
I can't.

180
00:15:35,018 --> 00:15:39,064
I got invited
to this country club thing.

181
00:15:39,106 --> 00:15:42,025
- Hey, that was fast.
- Yeah.

182
00:15:42,067 --> 00:15:44,444
Is that why you want
to learn Cuban dancing?

183
00:15:44,486 --> 00:15:45,863
Just to impress your date?

184
00:15:45,904 --> 00:15:47,823
No. I wanted to--

185
00:15:47,865 --> 00:15:48,824
Don't worry. Don't worry.

186
00:15:48,866 --> 00:15:50,576
They won't dance like that
at the club.

187
00:15:50,617 --> 00:15:53,120
Just learn
the fox trot instead.

188
00:15:54,454 --> 00:15:57,124
I already know the fox trot.

189
00:16:11,513 --> 00:16:13,765
Do we need to go shopping?

190
00:16:13,807 --> 00:16:15,434
I just thought you might
be going to the country club...

191
00:16:15,475 --> 00:16:17,561
Saturday night.

192
00:16:17,603 --> 00:16:19,146
Oh, you just thought?

193
00:16:19,188 --> 00:16:21,231
Mrs. Phelps took me to lunch.

194
00:16:21,273 --> 00:16:23,775
You two aren't planning
an arranged marriage, are you?

195
00:16:23,817 --> 00:16:25,194
No. I should have
thought of that.

196
00:16:26,862 --> 00:16:28,197
He's so cute.

197
00:16:40,083 --> 00:16:43,045
- Yolanda?
- Yes?

198
00:16:43,045 --> 00:16:46,173
Is this square?

199
00:16:46,215 --> 00:16:47,633
Square?

200
00:16:47,674 --> 00:16:51,303
Yeah, you know...
Iike a square?

201
00:16:51,345 --> 00:16:53,305
Is a square good or bad?

202
00:16:53,347 --> 00:16:55,474
It's bad.

203
00:16:55,516 --> 00:16:57,851
Sí.

204
00:16:57,893 --> 00:16:58,936
This is square.

205
00:16:58,977 --> 00:17:00,854
Oh, God.

206
00:17:02,231 --> 00:17:04,191
I don't know.

207
00:17:04,233 --> 00:17:07,444
You're smaller than me.
Your dresses'll be...

208
00:17:07,486 --> 00:17:09,655
Perfect.

209
00:17:11,782 --> 00:17:12,824
You're joking.

210
00:17:12,866 --> 00:17:15,494
Why? Is it square?

211
00:17:17,246 --> 00:17:18,997
Definitely not.

212
00:17:19,039 --> 00:17:22,125
It's not fair!

213
00:17:22,167 --> 00:17:23,627
All of my friends are going...

214
00:17:23,669 --> 00:17:25,337
so why would you go,
and I can't?

215
00:17:25,379 --> 00:17:28,549
I am older than you.

216
00:17:28,590 --> 00:17:31,927
Such a waste. You don't
even know how to have fun.

217
00:17:49,236 --> 00:17:50,946
Sure you don't
want me to stay?

218
00:17:52,364 --> 00:17:53,699
Dad, don't.

219
00:17:55,117 --> 00:17:56,743
OK. Bye.

220
00:18:01,623 --> 00:18:03,917
Be careful.

221
00:18:25,647 --> 00:18:28,108
Polly. Polly.

222
00:18:33,614 --> 00:18:36,033
God, what'd she do?
Paint it on?

223
00:18:36,074 --> 00:18:38,035
Señorita.

224
00:18:43,373 --> 00:18:44,374
Wow!

225
00:18:45,709 --> 00:18:47,336
Oh, I don't know.

226
00:18:47,377 --> 00:18:49,087
Oh, I do.

227
00:18:51,798 --> 00:18:53,509
I would like
to invite you all...

228
00:18:53,550 --> 00:18:55,427
to the Club Palace
on Christmas Eve--

229
00:18:55,469 --> 00:18:56,803
You been to the Palace yet?

230
00:18:56,845 --> 00:18:58,764
...the tenth annual
Latin ballroom...

231
00:18:58,805 --> 00:19:00,849
amateur dance contest.

232
00:19:00,891 --> 00:19:02,059
I'll have to take you.

233
00:19:11,026 --> 00:19:14,404
Oh, yeah, yeah

234
00:19:14,446 --> 00:19:15,531
Listen

235
00:19:15,572 --> 00:19:18,826
Darling, you

236
00:19:18,867 --> 00:19:21,578
Send me

237
00:19:21,620 --> 00:19:24,540
Darling, you

238
00:19:24,581 --> 00:19:26,166
Send me

239
00:19:26,208 --> 00:19:31,171
You feel really good.
Am I making you nervous?

240
00:19:31,213 --> 00:19:32,506
No.

241
00:19:32,548 --> 00:19:35,092
Well, you make me
a little nervous...

242
00:19:35,133 --> 00:19:40,222
but don't tell anyone.
It'll ruin my reputation.

243
00:19:40,264 --> 00:19:43,392
I thought it was infatuation

244
00:19:44,560 --> 00:19:46,228
Listen, we're going over
to Polly's...

245
00:19:46,270 --> 00:19:48,814
- for a little mojito party.
- Oh, yeah?

246
00:19:48,856 --> 00:19:50,858
And her parents
are out of town again.

247
00:19:50,899 --> 00:19:54,528
What do you think?
Steph can make a wicked mojito.

248
00:19:54,570 --> 00:19:56,446
Well--

249
00:19:56,488 --> 00:19:57,906
Hey, I'm sure
we can get someone...

250
00:19:57,948 --> 00:19:59,575
to rustle you up
a Shirley Temple.

251
00:20:01,577 --> 00:20:03,787
Actually...

252
00:20:03,829 --> 00:20:06,456
James and I are gonna
go to a Cuban club.

253
00:20:06,498 --> 00:20:07,499
Where?

254
00:20:08,959 --> 00:20:10,210
La Rosa Negra.

255
00:20:12,212 --> 00:20:15,674
Yeah, we're going to the...
La Rosa Negra.

256
00:20:27,436 --> 00:20:29,396
Jesus.

257
00:20:52,961 --> 00:20:54,922
Look at the way
they feel the music.

258
00:20:58,175 --> 00:21:00,302
They're feeling it,
all right.

259
00:21:04,181 --> 00:21:06,266
I'll get us some drinks.

260
00:21:37,297 --> 00:21:38,382
Hi.

261
00:21:40,217 --> 00:21:42,678
- You look so Cuban.
- So do you.

262
00:21:44,930 --> 00:21:47,057
Hi. I'm Javier.

263
00:21:48,267 --> 00:21:49,434
