01:00:53,654 --> 01:00:55,989
Katey, how could you think...

791
01:00:56,031 --> 01:00:58,325
that my job would be
more important than you?

792
01:00:59,910 --> 01:01:01,954
I didn't want to hurt you.

793
01:01:03,455 --> 01:01:08,168
I just wanted to help Javier,
which is his name, by the way.

794
01:01:10,921 --> 01:01:13,674
Oh, God,
I love dancing with him.

795
01:01:13,715 --> 01:01:16,343
Oh, Katey.

796
01:01:18,762 --> 01:01:22,683
Did it ever occur to you that
that boy might be using you?

797
01:01:22,724 --> 01:01:24,518
A nice American girl who can be
his ticket out of Havana?

798
01:01:24,560 --> 01:01:25,519
That's not true.

799
01:01:25,561 --> 01:01:26,562
You may love dancing
with that boy...

800
01:01:26,603 --> 01:01:27,729
but there are more
important factors here...

801
01:01:27,771 --> 01:01:30,023
Iike your family
and your future!

802
01:01:30,023 --> 01:01:31,233
Why does it have
to be either- or?

803
01:01:31,275 --> 01:01:33,735
Just because you gave up
your passion, why should I?

804
01:01:41,577 --> 01:01:43,537
Katey.

805
01:01:45,789 --> 01:01:47,749
Katey.

806
01:01:47,791 --> 01:01:50,210
Katey, wait. Honey, wait!

807
01:01:50,252 --> 01:01:51,587
I'm going to Javier's.

808
01:01:51,628 --> 01:01:53,463
Your mother's just trying
to protect you.

809
01:01:53,505 --> 01:01:54,882
I'm gonna be out there
on New Year's Eve...

810
01:01:54,923 --> 01:01:57,092
no matter what
you and Mom think.

811
01:01:57,134 --> 01:01:59,052
No more lies.

812
01:02:04,683 --> 01:02:06,727
He's out celebrating...

813
01:02:06,768 --> 01:02:10,939
so if you want
to wait for him...

814
01:02:16,612 --> 01:02:18,071
That was Katey.

815
01:02:20,699 --> 01:02:23,285
It's OK. She's with his mother.

816
01:02:23,327 --> 01:02:25,662
Was I wrong?

817
01:02:25,704 --> 01:02:27,581
No...

818
01:02:27,623 --> 01:02:29,458
but neither was Katey.

819
01:02:30,876 --> 01:02:32,377
Sometimes I wish we--

820
01:02:32,461 --> 01:02:36,465
I just try to imagine
what it would be like...

821
01:02:36,507 --> 01:02:38,800
if we hadn't had...

822
01:02:41,845 --> 01:02:43,889
Does it make me a bad mother?

823
01:02:43,972 --> 01:02:45,724
Of course not.

824
01:02:49,144 --> 01:02:52,231
You were good.
It's OK to miss it.

825
01:02:54,817 --> 01:02:57,361
They sure spiced up
our old routine, didn't they?

826
01:02:57,402 --> 01:02:58,821
I'll say.

827
01:02:58,862 --> 01:03:00,823
That wouldn't have gone over
too well at Roseland, would it?

828
01:03:00,864 --> 01:03:02,449
No.

829
01:03:05,202 --> 01:03:08,413
Bert, she's not
a little girl anymore.

830
01:03:28,851 --> 01:03:30,978
What are you reading?

831
01:03:33,730 --> 01:03:36,817
José Martí.

832
01:03:36,859 --> 01:03:37,985
It was my father's.

833
01:03:38,026 --> 01:03:42,114
We got rid of all his books
just to be safe, but...

834
01:03:42,156 --> 01:03:43,824
I kept this one.

835
01:03:45,159 --> 01:03:46,410
Hello.

836
01:03:47,536 --> 01:03:48,745
- Javier?
- Yeah?

837
01:03:50,914 --> 01:03:53,542
- If we don't win the finals--
- We will.

838
01:03:53,584 --> 01:03:56,044
But if we don't...

839
01:03:57,921 --> 01:04:00,007
I'm not gonna go to college
in six months.

840
01:04:03,927 --> 01:04:07,181
You don't know how
you're gonna feel in six months.

841
01:04:09,266 --> 01:04:10,517
Yes, I do.

842
01:04:12,436 --> 01:04:13,770
No, you don't.

843
01:04:15,230 --> 01:04:17,858
I don't want you
to give up your dreams for me.

844
01:04:17,900 --> 01:04:19,610
But I have new dreams now.

845
01:05:03,987 --> 01:05:06,615
Susie, why don't you and I go
raid that buffet by the pool?

846
01:05:06,657 --> 01:05:08,116
Sure.

847
01:05:20,379 --> 01:05:22,297
Tree looks nice.

848
01:05:28,679 --> 01:05:30,013
Your father and I
discussed it...

849
01:05:34,852 --> 01:05:37,104
and we think
that you should do...

850
01:05:37,146 --> 01:05:39,606
a double turn at the finals.

851
01:05:42,734 --> 01:05:44,194
You like the way I danced?

852
01:05:46,113 --> 01:05:48,907
Katey...

853
01:05:48,949 --> 01:05:52,619
if you're asking me to approve
of you and this boy, I can't.

854
01:05:52,619 --> 01:05:54,955
But the dancing...

855
01:05:57,833 --> 01:05:59,960
The dancing was incredible.

856
01:06:02,379 --> 01:06:04,965
I think I should take
a little credit for that.

857
01:06:06,884 --> 01:06:09,052
I think you should, too.

858
01:06:22,441 --> 01:06:23,734
- Hi!
- Hi!

859
01:06:25,277 --> 01:06:27,654
Javier, these are my parents.

860
01:06:27,654 --> 01:06:29,448
Hi, Javier.
It's nice to meet you.

861
01:06:29,490 --> 01:06:30,532
Nice to meet you, too.

862
01:06:30,574 --> 01:06:33,076
It's an honor to meet
such wonderful dancers.

863
01:06:33,118 --> 01:06:35,496
This is from my mother's garden.

864
01:06:35,496 --> 01:06:38,207
Thank you.
That was sweet of you.

865
01:06:38,248 --> 01:06:40,667
- This is for you.
- Thanks.

866
01:06:40,667 --> 01:06:43,003
- Shall we?
- Yeah.

867
01:06:43,545 --> 01:06:45,631
Tonight we bring you
the three winning couples...

868
01:06:45,672 --> 01:06:48,550
from the Latin ballroom
competition.

869
01:07:06,443 --> 01:07:08,779
Do you want to dance?

870
01:07:20,791 --> 01:07:22,084
Don't you dare!

871
01:07:48,652 --> 01:07:52,281
Feliz año nuevo,
ladies and gentlemen.

872
01:07:52,322 --> 01:07:57,786
Welcome to our Latin ballroom
amateur dance contest final.

873
01:08:02,416 --> 01:08:06,253
You will dance on the stage
one couple at a time.

874
01:08:06,295 --> 01:08:10,424
Tonight's winning couple
will win $5,000.

875
01:08:10,465 --> 01:08:13,093
You are up first.

876
01:08:13,135 --> 01:08:17,431
Our first couple this evening
is Mr. Jose Velarde...

877
01:08:17,473 --> 01:08:19,975
and Miss Iris Mesa!

878
01:08:52,758 --> 01:08:54,468
Don't forget
to look at the judges.

879
01:08:54,510 --> 01:08:56,345
Don't worry about the others.

880
01:08:56,386 --> 01:08:59,932
Remember, you're the queen
of La Rosa Negra.

881
01:09:01,225 --> 01:09:03,769
Our final contestants
this evening...

882
01:09:03,811 --> 01:09:07,397
Miss Katey Miller
and Mr. Javier Suarez.

883
01:10:07,249 --> 01:10:08,333
Sorry!

884
01:10:17,551 --> 01:10:19,136
He's got a gun!

885
01:10:19,178 --> 01:10:20,304
No!

886
01:10:28,896 --> 01:10:31,231
Go! I'll find you!

887
01:11:33,669 --> 01:11:35,128
No.

888
01:12:24,428 --> 01:12:26,513
Oye.

889
01:13:24,238 --> 01:13:28,700
¡Viva la revolución!

890
01:13:30,661 --> 01:13:32,579
Attention, all hotel guests.

891
01:13:32,621 --> 01:13:35,541
President Batista
has fled the country.

892
01:13:35,582 --> 01:13:39,795
There is no immediate danger.
Please contact the front desk...

893
01:14:07,573 --> 01:14:09,158
I can't believe it's real.

894
01:14:09,199 --> 01:14:11,618
Don't you wanna be
out there celebrating?

895
01:14:11,660 --> 01:14:15,164
No. I wanna be
right here with you.

896
01:15:22,731 --> 01:15:25,275
We didn't win the contest.

897
01:15:25,317 --> 01:15:27,736
No.

898
01:15:27,778 --> 01:15:30,781
But the consolation prize
was pretty good.

899
01:15:38,121 --> 01:15:42,042
I'm so happy
I can see all this with you.

900
01:15:50,050 --> 01:15:52,386
What?

901
01:15:52,386 --> 01:15:54,555
Nothing.

902
01:15:54,596 --> 01:15:56,223
Tell me.

903
01:15:58,851 --> 01:16:00,561
Carlos...

904
01:16:00,561 --> 01:16:04,148
he always said that
when the revolution came...

905
01:16:04,189 --> 01:16:07,401
Castro will kick out
all the Yankee companies.

906
01:16:09,945 --> 01:16:12,406
But you don't really know that.

907
01:16:12,406 --> 01:16:15,659
No. I'm just saying that...

908
01:16:15,701 --> 01:16:17,828
What, that I might
have to leave?

909
01:16:17,870 --> 01:16:20,747
It could happen.

910
01:16:20,747 --> 01:16:22,124
But they wouldn't do that...

911
01:16:22,166 --> 01:16:25,711
not if the whole idea
is to give people their freedom.

912
01:16:25,752 --> 01:16:27,504
Cuban people.

913
01:16:29,131 --> 01:16:31,884
Well, then,
you'll come with us.

914
01:16:31,925 --> 01:16:33,427
I'm sure my dad
can work it out.

915
01:16:33,469 --> 01:16:35,512
And my family?

916
01:16:35,554 --> 01:16:37,931
We'll send for them, just like
we were always gonna do.

917
01:16:37,973 --> 01:16:41,435
Katey, I wanted to leave
because of Batista, but now--

918
01:16:41,477 --> 01:16:43,270
But you don't know
what life will be like here.

919
01:16:43,312 --> 01:16:45,272
I mean, what if
it doesn't get better?

920
01:16:46,982 --> 01:16:49,067
My father died for this.

921
01:16:49,109 --> 01:16:51,153
I have to believe it will.

922
01:16:52,821 --> 01:16:55,073
I can make a difference here.

923
01:16:55,115 --> 01:16:56,825
You showed me that.

924
01:16:59,411 --> 01:17:02,206
This is my country.
It's my home.

925
01:17:10,214 --> 01:17:11,840
Oh, thank God.

926
01:17:11,882 --> 01:17:13,509
Katey, are you OK?

927
01:17:15,385 --> 01:17:17,137
We're leaving.

928
01:17:17,137 --> 01:17:19,515
Yeah. Your father's
making arrangements.

929
01:17:39,409 --> 01:17:41,662
Give me that comb.

930
01:17:43,831 --> 01:17:45,791
When you were little, you used
to hide under the bed...

931
01:17:45,833 --> 01:17:48,794
when I'd try
to comb out these knots.

932
01:17:56,009 --> 01:17:58,011
Katey, your father's been
the only man in my life...

933
01:17:58,053 --> 01:18:02,141
so I don't know what it's like
to say good-bye to someone.

934
01:18:02,182 --> 01:18:06,395
Saying good-bye to dancing,
the other love of my life...

935
01:18:09,356 --> 01:18:10,899
it broke my heart.

936
01:18:16,989 --> 01:18:18,991
Then you were born,
and then Susie...

937
01:18:19,032 --> 01:18:21,118
and I loved you both
so much that I--

938
01:18:21,160 --> 01:18:24,872
- You're saying I'll get over it.
- No, I'm not. No.

939
01:18:26,957 --> 01:18:29,126
No. I'm saying
I know you're hurting.

940
01:18:30,544 --> 01:18:32,421
Everything's such a mess.

941
01:18:34,631 --> 01:18:37,009
You have a choice.

942
01:18:37,050 --> 01:18:38,886
You can do nothing.

943
01:18:38,886 --> 01:18:42,222
You can hide under the bed...

944
01:18:42,264 --> 01:18:44,850
Or you can
work through the knots.

945
01:19:08,123 --> 01:19:09,750
I'm gonna miss you.

946
01:19:14,588 --> 01:19:16,256
I'm gonna miss you, too.

947
01:19:18,175 --> 01:19:21,011
I am taking you with me.

948
01:19:21,053 --> 01:19:23,806
I am keeping you here.

949
01:19:59,299 --> 01:20:01,135
Javier once said
that dancing...

950
01:20:01,135 --> 01:20:04,513
is about being exactly who
you wanna be in that moment.

951
01:20:04,555 --> 01:20:07,224
Dancing with him,
I realized I was becoming...

952
01:20:07,266 --> 01:20:10,102
exactly the woman
I wanted to be.

953
01:20:10,144 --> 01:20:11,645
We didn't win the contest...

954
01:20:11,687 --> 01:20:13,981
but we did win something
more important to us.

955
01:20:14,022 --> 01:20:15,816
On my last night in Havana...

956
01:20:15,858 --> 01:20:19,027
we were king and queen
of La Rosa Negra.

957
01:21:21,465 --> 01:21:23,884
We didn't know when
we would see each other again...

958
01:21:23,884 --> 01:21:26,970
but we knew that this
wasn't our last dance.

